<section class="banner-section-service"></section>
<section class="container px-4 py-5">
    <div class="row p-4 pb-0 pe-lg-0 pt-lg-5 align-items-center">
        <div class="col-lg-7 text-center text-lg-start ">
            <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold lh-1 mb-3 ">VAT Refunds Services in the UAE</h1>
            <nav aria-label="breadcrumb" class="breadcrumb-text">
                <ol class="breadcrumb">
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a asp-action="Index" asp-controller="Home">Home</a> /</li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">VAT Refunds Services in the UAE</li>
                </ol>
            </nav>
            <hr class="my-4">
            <h2>Maximize Your VAT Refund with Experts help</h2>
            <p class="col-lg-10 fs-4">
                As per the VAT laws in the UAE, it is mandatory for taxable entities and companies to submit their VAT Return 
                by filling out the required form provided by the Federal Tax Authority (FTA). The deadline for filing VAT returns 
                is 28 days from the end of each tax period. 
                Failure to do so can result in hefty fines.
            </p>
            <p class="col-lg-10 fs-4">
                To ensure proper compliance, there is a specific procedure for VAT Return filing that must be followed.
                This process can be completed by the taxable entity or through
                a qualified and experienced tax agent.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-10 mx-auto col-lg-5 pb-3  ">
            <img src="/assets/images/services/ser-9.jpg" alt="Accounting Firm in Dubai" class="img-fluid rounded-3 mb-3 ">

            @await Html.PartialAsync("_AsideContact")
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

